                <h2><a href="https://kk.org/cooltools/cheap-dremel-clone/">Cheap Dremel Clone</a></h2>
                <h3>Low price rotary tool</h3>

                
                <p>I&#8217;ve been using this <a href="https://geni.us/rotary-tool">Wen rotary tool</a> for a few months and I&#8217;m really happy with it. It&#8217;s much cheaper than a Dremel tool and accepts Dremel bits, which I already have in abundance. If you don&#8217;t have any Dremel bits, no problem &#8212; it comes with a good starter assortment. The flexible shaft is an added bonus, because it gives you more control than holding the tool itself. It&#8217;s a great way to rough out the shape of wooden spoons I&#8217;ve been whittling:</p>
